      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Nefarietteeci</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Hello!</P><P>I started about 4 months ago thinking that faster running speed would save the day for me. I saved up (camped Gornit on and off for 2 months to level 47, I think) and earned enough to buy a pair of T-boots. (camping the AC has always been something that I’ve been very adverse to, I don’t know why exactly.) So Anyway, I finally saved up about 6K and headed off to SolA. Unfortunately I found that the merchant didn’t like me much, so I was out of luck. The only way to raise the faction was to hunt in SolB. I really only like to solo, so that was pretty much out.</P><P>In the end I decided  to buy a horse. I could only afford a cheap rope bridle one, but I did fork out the bonus 1K or so for a black horse.</P><P>I’ve found it to be pretty good on the whole, but found out quick that it really won’t help you in outrunning mobs. If you’re running from mobs you can just get ahead of them, but you won’t make any ground. They won’t be able to hit you (as long as you’re running in a straight line), but you definitely won’t lose them. I’ve been suffering from 1-2 sec lag spikes for the last month or two, and that’s all it takes for 4 halfling guards to catch up and kill you before you can even feign.</P><P>The acceleration and deceleration thing can be a problem too, but after a while you do get used to it.</P><P>I used the horse mostly for getting from here to there, and it works well enough for that. SoW potions would probably be better all around, but I like to keep my dependence on other players to a minimum, and I’m a sucker for anything that has a cool effect and limitless charges.</P><P>However, in the past couple weeks, I’ve found that the horse can be used very strategically when hunting. The casting time is only a couple seconds, so it’s easy to pull it up when you want it and drop it when you don’t. I often found myself pulling a mob with darkness, sending in the pet, casting a horse, then casting a fear or DoT. If you need to swap any spells, no problem, you don’t suffer from the med aggro, whenever you’re standing still it counts as sitting for mana recovery which helps with downtime without having to worry about sitting and standing during a fight. You’re always ready to cast the next spell whatever it is. </P><P>There are lots of negatives to the horse, but there it is also quite possible to develop a nice technique where the two of you can work together in harmony for the destruction of all that is good and holy.</P><P>Turning off the Luclin graphics is a stroke of genius that I had never thought of, and will certainly look into, although I must say that a skeleton carrying a scythe riding a black horse looks pretty damned cool.</P><P>All in all, I’m very happy with the horse, and it’s fun to figure out ways to use it to your advantage, but at the same time, it does not fulfil my main desire in purchasing it: the ability to outrun mobs. Also, the invis part is tricky. Sometimes it works sometimes it doesn’t. Twice I had a horse, invised, then traveled through the combine pots, zoned and was attacked (and killed) by guards. Always be sure to con them before running past ‘em.</P><P>Oh, one other point: When riding a horse, you retain the same running speed no matter how encumbered you are. You can sit back and fill all your bags with fine steel, and carry 20,000 copper and still run at full tilt. That’s a nice little bonus, especially for those of us who feel very guilty destroying gold.</P><P>Two requests:<BR>1. If anyone has any other clever techniques for how to use a horse to your advantage, please let me know<BR>2. If I were to pool all my money, camp some more for a week or two and trade in my beautiful black horse, I might be able to afford an upgrade to a leather bridle (only a brown one though, this time). Do you think this would be worthwhile? I’m very slow at earning cash (don’t like to sell on auction, but do love to buy), so it would be a monumental decision. </P><P>Nefariette<BR>51 Heretic<BR>E’ci</P><P><BR> </font></td>
