 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Infectar</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Back when cheese making was a great cash venture I made cheese until I nearly went blind and crazy and earned enough cash to buy myself a horse.  It was without doubt one of the worst decisions I have ever made in almost three years of playing EQ.  The start/stop time make casting on the fly almost impossible.  At higher levels increased channeling skill might compensate a bit but I doubt it.  The fricking horse head parked right in the middle of the screen was distracting and more than a bit reminiscent of The Godfather.  In short I hated the damn thing.  Off to the vendor to sell it back only to discover that I had moved from Francis Ford to Q. Tarantino.  I found myself in the back room of a store being reamed by a psycho salesman.  The sell back price is terrible, it cost me about 2k of my hard earned "cheese money".  From my experience all I can say is "DON'T BUY A HORSE"</P><P>After this horrible experience I too decided that I would use my remaining cash to purchase a pair of T-Boots.  After running into faction problems I came here and got the best piece of advice I could.  Go for J-Boots. I got them and I love them.  If the horse was one of my worst moves the J-Boots were certainly one of the best (and because I actually camped them as opposed to MQ'ing them I got to keep my cheese money).  </P><P>Obviously some of the problems I encountered with the horse would have been offset by turning off the Luclin graphics but being a Luclin user since the day it first went live I have no intention of giving up what I have paid so dearly for not so much with money but with all the hair I have ripped out of my scalp and the three ulcers that this ungodly expansion has produced. Also I can't help but believe that this little work around flys directly in the face of what VI intends for horses and at some date in the future it will be nerfed away.  If you are lucky enough to have a friend who owns a horse ask to try their's out first in person or by sharing their account access (yeah I know it's prohibited). Who knows maybe your experience will be different than mine.</P><P> </font></td>
